      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy test demonstrates at least first-order convergence for momentum and scalar transport equations.",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to the Navier-Stokes and hemolysis scalar transport equations. Observed order of accuracy of 1.92 confirmed, consistent with second-order spatial discretization."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for hemolysis index QoI below 5%.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (4.2 M, 8.7 M, 17.1 M cells). GCI for the hemolysis index at the design operating point is 3.1%, meeting the acceptance criterion. Medium mesh adopted for production runs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
