      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Hemolysis index directly linked to the regulatory decision metric for Class II blood-contacting devices.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) is the primary regulatory QoI per ISO 10993-4 and FDA guidance. CFD-predicted NIH maps directly to the worst-case operating point identification decision."
